    "description": "Breakfast doesn't get any heartier or more satisfying than this home-style classic. No one will leave the table hungry! â€”John Wilhelm, Richmond, Virginia",
    "recipeIngredient": [
        "2 pounds bulk pork sausage",
        "1/3 cup all-purpose flour",
        "3 teaspoons pepper",
        "2 teaspoons sugar",
        "1/2 teaspoon salt",
        "2 cups 2% milk",
        "2 cans (5 ounces each) evaporated milk",
        "Cooked biscuits"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "text": "In a Dutch oven, cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink, breaking into crumbles (do not drain), 8-10 minutes. Add flour, pepper, sugar and salt; cook and stir until blended, about 2 minutes."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "text": "Stir in milks; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until thickened, 3-5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with biscuits."
        }
    ],
